However, you do already have lots of stability from &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;1667&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Martial Cadence&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;rotation-and-utilities&quot;&gt;Rotation and Utilities&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;general-concept&quot;&gt;General concept&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The build relies on the auto chain, which is just F1 (press and hold). This will provide a baseline DPS of 21-23k (when a couple of long-lasting passives are triggered).
The build can be enhanced further by triggering relics, signets and traits through a sequence of skills which constitutes the basics of playing warrior, combos. The combo is a tight chain of skills that eventually builds up to an extremely buffed chain of attacks.
Almost every warrior build will require learning of combos to trigger effects, otherwise you will remain at the baseline auto attack DPS or lower. These effects are simplified and broken down into the table below, sorted based on the duration of effect from longest&#x2F;permanent effects to shortest:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;&lt;thead&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;th&gt;Effect&lt;&#x2F;th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Notes&lt;&#x2F;th&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;&lt;&#x2F;thead&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;2095&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Sun and Moon Style&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Dagger MH (+ OH Heals)&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;1437&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Berserker&#x27;s Power&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Bursts (15s, 4 stacks)&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;2130&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Attacker&#x27;s Insight&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Disables (15s, 5 stacks)&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;100916&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;Â Relic of the Thief&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Skills 2-5 (6s, 5 stacks)&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;1444&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Peak Performance&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Physical skill (6s)&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14410&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Signet of Fury&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Active window (4s)&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;tbody&gt;&lt;&#x2F;table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The attack duration means you need to trigger these effect somewhat loosely from the top and more tightly towards the bottom. This means &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14410&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Signet of Fury&#x27;s window must be triggered right before using your heaviest damage skills during your opener&#x2F;during the last hits. The passive effect of &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14410&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Signet of Fury is lost when its used, hence its only used when its most beneficial, during the opener or final blows.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;small&gt;By default, warrior is not a button mashing class and it would be recommended to refine your play better as you get used to this build so that you can adapt to weapon swaps and other weapons.&lt;&#x2F;small&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;opener&quot;&gt;Opener&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Precast &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;45333&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Winds of Disenchantment for the lightning field which provides extra disables and &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;2130&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Attacker&#x27;s Insight stacks with the other movement skills.
Early stacks of Brutal Bolts can stack vulnerability faster on bosses at the start of the fight, increasing group DPS.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;small&gt;Some players use &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14402&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; &quot;To the Limit!&quot; to build up adrenaline although in the video &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14410&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Signet of Fury is used instead in the opener.&lt;&#x2F;small&gt;&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;small&gt;If you decide not to take &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;45333&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Winds of Disenchantment, you may need to remove &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14410&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Signet of Fury from the opener as the dps gain from low stacks of &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;2130&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Attacker&#x27;s Insight may not justify the DPS loss from the signet downtime.&lt;&#x2F;small&gt;&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;dps-rotation&quot;&gt;DPS Rotation&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Start with Dagger&#x2F;Axe&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opener - &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;45333&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Winds of Disenchantment -&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14516&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Bull&#x27;s Charge -&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;46233&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Aura Slicer -&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14410&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Signet of Fury -&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;45252&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Breaching Strike -&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14399&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Whirling Axe&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintenance - skills 1-5 + &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14516&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Bull&#x27;s Charge on cooldown&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Finisher - &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14410&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Signet of Fury -&amp;gt; skills in the following order:
a. &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;45252&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Breaching Strike
b. &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14399&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Whirling Axe
c. &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14418&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Dual Strike
d. &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;44937&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Disrupting Stab&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;small&gt;&lt;em&gt;You may extend the auto chain cycle if you need a break. If you need to reorientate yourself (or if you have a pizza on your other hand), you may also extend the auto-chain indefinitely by just holding F1 and it will still do a base of 23k DPS at 0 APM (while attacker&#x27;s insight is still up)&lt;&#x2F;em&gt;&lt;&#x2F;small&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;crowd-control-rotation&quot;&gt;Crowd Control rotation&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have decent CC by using &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;44937&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Disrupting Stab (dagger 3) and &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14410&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Signet of Fury&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14502&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Kick is the preferred CC skill if you can hit more than 1 enemy at once&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full Counter provides breakbar damage too and is useful if you know the fight well.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opener chain uses &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;46233&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Aura Slicer for lightning field finishers to generate lots of daze that do heavy CC.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consider hammer as an alternative weapon set (refer to Snowcrow&#x27;s)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;sustainability&quot;&gt;Sustainability&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Your OH dagger set is designed for sustain and you may sselect it if you do not have good heal access (eg. your healer blinked through Soulless Horror&#x27;s Wall&#x2F;Your heal tank got knocked away by Deimos).&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Defiant stance can be taken instead to cheese certain mechanics (see &lt;em&gt;Raid Ready&lt;&#x2F;em&gt; section)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;optimisation&quot;&gt;Optimisation&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This build has no ranged alternative. However, based on my personal testing, this build does more damage on mobile fights (like Twin Largos) than Condition Berserker. If you find yourself being forced out of range often and can&#x27;t manage to cope, you might want to play a different class.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;raid-ready&quot;&gt;Raid Ready&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W1 Vale Guardian - &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;45252&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Breaching Strike(F1) does a boon strip that can be used on the Blue Boss.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W1 Gorseval - &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14354&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Throw Bolas is a really long immobilise that can extend the split phase. If using MH Axe, you can &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14398&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Throw Axe to do a ranged cripple.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W2 Slothasor - You can bring permanent self stability via &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;1447&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Brave Stride and drop your physical skills for party wide Break Stuns and Condi Cleanses if the group needs it.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W3 Keep Construct - This build is excellent on this fight. Using &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14502&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Kick can hit more than one target and pile up multiple stacks of &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;2130&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Attacker&#x27;s Insight.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W3 Xera - During planning for the split phase, you want to inform your party that you do not have any meaningful ranged damage. If forced to take a pressure pad, your only damage skills are &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14398&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Throw Axe which is effectively neglible.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W4 Cairn - In the dagger OH alt set, &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;45160&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Bladestorm(D5) is a reflect, don&#x27;t use it in this fight.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W4 Deimos - &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14354&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Throw Bolas at prides is an effective way to keep Saul alive as part of your rotation. I do not recommending killing the prides until they are next to Saul as they will respawn. &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;21815&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Defiant Stance is also a simple one-button mind crush deflector if you are going to be the oil kiter.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W5 Soulless Horror - It is probably not good idea to bring the build here. If you do however, do not use Axe 5 when TD is about to spawn. Do the burst combo after TD is pushed out.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W6 Conjured Amalgamate - The amount of cleave on this fight is amazing. Use &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14502&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Kick on swords and shields, and most of the time you can hit more than 1 target at once. You can use &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;21815&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Defiant Stance and &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14419&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Battle Standard  to bypass the clap mechanic for your subgroup.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W6 Qadim - You can solo lamp on this build using FC and OH dagger to heal. If lamping with &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;1447&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Brave Stride for perma stability on the giant fight, you can drop your physical skills for other skills such as &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14389&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Healing Signet&#x2F;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14413&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Dolyak Signet for better survivability. While this is slower than shortbow daredevil, it is easier to perform. WoD is also very useful against the main boss fight in the middle if stability pyre is to be ignored.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;videos&quot;&gt;Videos&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I have benched the build with 1 piece of marauder&#x27;s headgear, budget food and utilities, no infusions.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
